                                                                                                       •   Generated by one entity and provided to another entity using an automated key-
                                                                                                           transport scheme (see Sections 5.3.4 and 5.3.5).
                                                                                                SP 800-56C and SP 800-135 84 provide methods for deriving keys from the shared secrets
                                                                                                generated during key agreement (see Section 5.3.3).
                                                                                                5.3.3      Key Agreement
                                                                                                Key agreement is a key-establishment procedure in which the resultant keying material is
                                                                                                a function of information contributed by all participants in the key-agreement process so
                                                                                                that no participant can predetermine the value of the resulting keying material independent
                                                                                                of the contributions of the other participants. Key agreement is usually performed using
                                                                                                automated protocols.
                                                                                                SP 800-56A and SP 800-56B provide several automated pair-wise key-agreement schemes
                                                                                                (i.e., key-agreement schemes involving two parties). For each scheme, a shared secret is
                                                                                                generated, and keying material is derived from the shared secret using a key-derivation
                                                                                                method specified or approved in SP 800-56C.
                                                                                                SP 800-56A and SP 800-56B include variations of key-agreement schemes differing in the
                                                                                                number of keys used and whether the keys are long term (i.e., static) or an ephemeral value
                                                                                                (e.g., a nonce or a short-term key pair). The key-agreement schemes have two participating
                                                                                                entities: an initiator and a responder.




